But no.

27:30.760 --> 27:32.800
The beer company love the clip.

27:35.240 --> 27:36.400
What?

27:38.760 --> 27:39.920
It's Dwayne.

27:39.960 --> 27:42.080
Ask Cheryl. Check with the company.

27:42.120 --> 27:43.960
Ask anyone. I thought, yes,

27:44.000 --> 27:46.480
him gobbing off had ruined it

27:44.000 --> 27:46.480
for all of us again.

27:46.520 --> 27:48.240
But she was on the phone to 'em this morning.

27:48.280 --> 27:50.320
They think it's hilarious.

27:50.360 --> 27:52.320
Proper rock 'n' roll.

27:52.360 --> 27:55.160
Pure Stevie. No such thing as bad press.

27:55.200 --> 27:57.240
You know what I mean? Go figure.

27:58.840 --> 28:00.120
Right.

28:00.160 --> 28:02.800
Er, well, thank you for your time, Mr Thunders.

28:06.840 --> 28:08.560
Right, we need to check with the beer company.

28:08.600 --> 28:09.680
But if Pete's telling the truth

28:09.720 --> 28:11.000
about their reaction to the footage,

28:11.040 --> 28:13.040
then we've just lost ourselves a motive.

28:13.080 --> 28:16.720
Then you'll be pleased to know we might have found

28:13.080 --> 28:16.720
another one.

28:16.760 --> 28:20.440
Dwayne heard from the hotel. The porter's arrived for work.

28:20.480 --> 28:23.280
We know who Stevie was arguing with in his bedroom.

28:23.320 --> 28:25.120
Who was it?

28:25.160 --> 28:27.400
Oh, yeah. Hang on.

28:27.440 --> 28:29.560
I do remember some little busybody porter

28:29.600 --> 28:30.880
banging on Stevie's door,

28:30.920 --> 28:32.920
mouthing off about summat.

28:38.320 --> 28:40.000
Did you threaten to kill Stevie?

28:41.800 --> 28:44.640
Oh, right. Er, I don't know.

28:44.680 --> 28:46.280
Might have, yeah.

28:46.320 --> 28:48.280
Well, we say it all the time, right?

28:48.320 --> 28:49.720
I mean, I wouldn't actually kill him.

28:49.760 --> 28:50.880
He's like a brother to me.

28:52.160 --> 28:54.000
He is your brother.

28:54.040 --> 28:55.240
Yeah, it's right, that.

28:56.840 --> 28:59.400
What were you fighting about?

28:59.440 --> 29:02.440
I can't remember. Summat and nothing, I suppose.

29:02.480 --> 29:04.400
-I'm not.

29:04.440 --> 29:06.600
Neatly pressed shirt.

29:06.640 --> 29:08.880
Boots mid-polish on the table.

29:10.760 --> 29:13.320
Must be going somewhere you want to make an impression.

29:13.360 --> 29:16.680
I'm just going around and about.

29:16.720 --> 29:19.760
Soak up a bit of the Caribbean vibe

29:16.720 --> 29:19.760
and that, yeah?

29:19.800 --> 29:22.960
So, if you've got no more questions...

29:24.960 --> 29:26.240
DWAYNE: <i> You think</i> <i>he's hiding something?</i>

29:26.280 --> 29:28.200
Yeah, it's possible.

29:28.240 --> 29:30.880
He clearly didn't want us to know what his argument

29:28.240 --> 29:30.880
with Stevie was about.

29:30.920 --> 29:34.040
And he was very cagey about where he was going tonight.

29:34.080 --> 29:35.720
Hang on a minute.

29:35.760 --> 29:39.240
On the recording, Jim was asking

29:35.760 --> 29:39.240
something about a bar.

29:39.280 --> 29:41.640
Bullet Bar. Maybe that's where he's going.

29:41.680 --> 29:43.440
You want us to head down there and see what he's up to?

29:43.480 --> 29:45.560
A little light surveillance might not hurt at all.

29:45.600 --> 29:46.720
Thank you, Dwayne.

29:48.000 --> 29:50.360
Er, the post-mortem reports have come through.

29:50.400 --> 29:51.720
They've confirmed Stevie suffered

29:51.760 --> 29:53.680
sudden cardiac arrest due to electrocution,

29:53.720 --> 29:55.280
and they're not disputing the time of death.

29:55.320 --> 29:57.760
So, we now know for definite that he was

29:55.320 --> 29:57.760
murdered at 12:00.

29:57.800 --> 30:00.320
Right, you'd better get changed and head

29:57.800 --> 30:00.320
over to the Bullet Bar.

30:00.360 --> 30:01.360
Chief.

30:03.040 --> 30:05.880
Stevie was killed at noon.

30:05.920 --> 30:07.320
The recording we have confirms

30:07.360 --> 30:09.640
that our five suspects were all together at that time.

30:09.680 --> 30:11.080
But someone had to have been by the pool

30:11.120 --> 30:13.280
to push the stage lights in and electrocute Stevie.

30:13.320 --> 30:14.440
Who was it and how?

30:16.040 --> 30:18.200
And what about you, little fella?

30:21.080 --> 30:22.360
How did you get there?

30:23.880 --> 30:26.440
I found the fan magazine you were talking about online.

30:26.480 --> 30:28.560
<i>-The Flower Seeds.</i> -Oh! Good work, Florence.

30:28.600 --> 30:31.320
There's quite a few editions. Shall we take half each?

30:31.360 --> 30:33.240
That's almost a very good idea.

30:33.280 --> 30:34.600
-Yes.

30:34.640 --> 30:36.160
In order to make it a truly brilliant idea,

30:36.200 --> 30:37.680
you might have added that we take half each,

30:37.720 --> 30:39.360
decamp to Catherine's Bar, and read them there.

30:39.400 --> 30:42.760
-I'd say that is

30:39.400 --> 30:42.760
a much better idea.

30:42.800 --> 30:44.400
Excellent.

31:01.120 --> 31:03.440
We're not allowed to drink on duty, are we?

31:03.480 --> 31:05.080
It's so we can blend in.

31:05.120 --> 31:07.560
I'm very dedicated to my undercover work,

31:05.120 --> 31:07.560
you know.

31:09.480 --> 31:11.680
I mean, very, very dedicated.

31:13.000 --> 31:15.160
Raise them high, drain them dry.

31:19.080 --> 31:21.640
Only I'm not really

31:19.080 --> 31:21.640
a big drinker, sir.

31:21.680 --> 31:23.320
You know how it is.

31:23.360 --> 31:25.320
No, I don't. Now, get it down you.

31:30.800 --> 31:33.040
Soothe your throat with your beer, the man!

31:37.320 --> 31:38.360
Look.

31:38.400 --> 31:41.760
No, don't look. He's meeting someone.

31:41.800 --> 31:43.920
-Bide our time.

31:43.960 --> 31:48.040
If they separate, I'll tail the woman.

31:43.960 --> 31:48.040
You follow Jim. Okay?

31:51.680 --> 31:53.480
Edited by Daisy Buttercup.

31:58.840 --> 32:01.440
Photography by Daisy Buttercup.

31:58.840 --> 32:01.440
Articles on the band by...

32:01.480 --> 32:04.120
-Oh, she's not real.

32:04.160 --> 32:05.360
It's a song on the first album,

32:05.400 --> 32:07.000
and not a particularly good one at that.

32:07.040 --> 32:09.920
It was clearly a one-nutty-fan operation.

32:09.960 --> 32:13.200
You're a fan. Are you Daisy Buttercup?

32:13.240 --> 32:14.520
Yes, I am not a fan.

32:14.560 --> 32:16.560
Just following Angela Matterson's orders?

32:18.800 --> 32:20.720
Did anything ever happen between you and Angela?

32:20.760 --> 32:23.440
Oh, gosh, no, no, no. We... We never even held hands.

32:23.480 --> 32:25.920
Ah, perhaps it wasn't a bad thing.

32:25.960 --> 32:28.120
Life would have spun me off in a different direction.

32:28.160 --> 32:29.720
I certainly wouldn't be here.

32:33.000 --> 32:35.400
You have your own male Angela Matterson?

32:35.440 --> 32:37.680
Not quite. My five brothers.

32:37.720 --> 32:42.240
If ever I brought a boy to the house, they always

32:37.720 --> 32:42.240
managed to scare him off.

32:42.280 --> 32:44.200
-Simple, really.

32:44.240 --> 32:47.160
I stopped taking my boyfriends back

32:44.240 --> 32:47.160
to meet my brothers.

32:47.200 --> 32:48.800
Touche.

32:49.680 --> 32:51.760
JP! Jim's on the move!

33:07.360 --> 33:09.240
You'd better follow him.

33:09.280 --> 33:12.640
JP! Ah, man! What am I meant to do now?

33:14.080 --> 33:15.160
Ah.

33:16.120 --> 33:18.600
Er, excuse me, miss.

33:18.640 --> 33:21.960
My young and, er, very inexperienced friend here

33:22.000 --> 33:24.280
has had a little too much to drink.

33:24.320 --> 33:27.800
But I must finish these before I leave.

33:27.840 --> 33:30.360
Would you be so kind as to help me with them?

33:44.520 --> 33:45.560
Oh, I see. Er, well, yes,

33:45.600 --> 33:47.320
a kind of a trip, although not for me.

33:47.360 --> 33:48.960
And it's, erm, sort of already happened.

33:51.560 --> 33:53.680
Our friend, the click beetle.

33:53.720 --> 33:55.440
Trying to work out whether it's possible

33:55.480 --> 33:58.120
he could have made the journey between

33:55.480 --> 33:58.120
Martinique and Saint-Marie.

33:58.680 --> 34:00.080
And?

34:00.120 --> 34:02.160
Well, it's a good 70 miles between the two islands and,

34:02.200 --> 34:06.600
while click beetles can fly, it's really only at night,

34:02.200 --> 34:06.600
and really rather rare.

34:06.640 --> 34:09.920
Maybe he ended up on a boat or a plane

34:06.640 --> 34:09.920
and got carried over.

34:09.960 --> 34:11.680
Yes, well, I've also looked into that.

34:11.720 --> 34:14.040
Um, all planes leaving the Caribbean

34:14.080 --> 34:17.160
are sprayed with insecticides before departure.

34:17.200 --> 34:19.160
Well, he would have been dead before he left Martinique.

34:19.200 --> 34:22.000
Well, you've certainly been very thorough.

34:23.480 --> 34:26.080
Do you think maybe we should...

34:26.120 --> 34:27.760
Oh, yes, yes. Yes, of course. Quite right.

34:41.120 --> 34:42.760
Don't even think about it.

34:45.760 --> 34:49.160
So, we know the night before his murder,

34:45.760 --> 34:49.160
Stevie was fighting with Jim.

34:49.200 --> 34:51.480
The two of them have always had a stormy relationship,

34:51.520 --> 34:55.320
but we don't know specifically what this argument was about.

34:55.360 --> 34:57.480
Vince. Stevie burnt his studio down.

34:57.520 --> 35:00.440
And, as we know from insurance checks,

34:57.520 --> 35:00.440
he wasn't covered.

35:00.480 --> 35:01.920
Quite.

35:01.960 --> 35:03.640
-Morning, all. -Morning. How did you

35:01.960 --> 35:03.640
get on last night?

35:03.680 --> 35:05.320
Oh, pretty good, Chief.

35:05.360 --> 35:07.920
Exactly like you thought, Jim turned up to

35:05.360 --> 35:07.920
the Bullet Bar,

35:07.960 --> 35:09.680
where he met and had a drink with a woman.

35:09.720 --> 35:11.760
Right. Did you manage to find out who she was?

35:11.800 --> 35:13.320
More than that, Chief.

35:13.360 --> 35:16.240
Her name was Marie Etner.

35:16.280 --> 35:20.000
She was a girl Jim knew from the last time the band were

35:16.280 --> 35:20.000
on the island back in 1991.

35:20.040 --> 35:22.160
Er, she and Jim had a bit of a thing, you know?

35:22.200 --> 35:23.760
Ah, interesting. Go on.

35:23.800 --> 35:25.240
DWAYNE: Well, that's only the start.

35:25.280 --> 35:28.240
Turns out she fell pregnant and had his kid.

35:28.280 --> 35:29.800
-Oh, no, no, no, no.

35:29.840 --> 35:31.400
Jim never even knew he was the father,

35:31.440 --> 35:32.920
not until the day before yesterday.

35:32.960 --> 35:35.080
-I... I don't understand. -DWAYNE: Look.

35:35.120 --> 35:37.280
When Marie found out she was pregnant,

35:35.120 --> 35:37.280
she called Jim.

35:37.320 --> 35:40.880
But she could only get hold of Stevie, and he promised

35:37.320 --> 35:40.880
to pass the message on.

35:40.920 --> 35:42.120
And what

35:42.160 --> 35:44.560
-No. -So, let me get this right.

35:44.600 --> 35:47.720
Stevie was never going to tell his own brother

35:44.600 --> 35:47.720
he was going to be a dad?

35:47.760 --> 35:50.680
Exactly. He only found out about it two days ago.

35:50.720 --> 35:52.960
That must be why they were arguing in Stevie's room.

35:53.000 --> 35:54.480
-Good work, Dwayne. -Thank you, Chief.

35:54.520 --> 35:57.080
Florence, I think you and I need to go and speak to Jim.

35:57.120 --> 35:59.880
-I am really sorry, everyone...

35:59.920 --> 36:02.320
Er, Jim's still in his room, yeah?

36:03.520 --> 36:05.400
Er, good work. Right, Chief?

36:06.360 --> 36:08.000
Yes.

36:08.040 --> 36:10.920
Come on, Florence!

36:10.960 --> 36:14.120
-DWAYNE: Sarge. -I... I overslept. I was going

36:10.960 --> 36:14.120
to come clean and...

36:14.160 --> 36:18.280
And I covered for you. It's what they don't teach you

36:14.160 --> 36:18.280
at police college.

36:18.320 --> 36:20.240
We are a team.

36:20.280 --> 36:23.280
So, I'll be counting on you to do exactly the same thing

36:20.280 --> 36:23.280
for me next Thursday, when I'm recovering

36:23.320 --> 36:26.320
from Domino Club and a few large rums.

36:26.360 --> 36:28.240
Now, get yourself an aspirin and get to it.

36:28.280 --> 36:30.440
We got a lot of work to do.

36:30.480 --> 36:31.840
Chop chop!

36:40.000 --> 36:42.960
You didn't get on well, you and Stevie?

36:43.000 --> 36:46.040
We had a couple of fallouts and the press built it up,

36:43.000 --> 36:46.040
yeah?

36:46.080 --> 36:47.240
It was nothing serious.

36:47.280 --> 36:48.680
-No!

36:48.720 --> 36:50.000
Even when he kept things from you?

36:52.600 --> 36:54.240
Like you becoming a father?

36:57.320 --> 36:58.320
You spoke with Marie?

37:06.280 --> 37:09.360
It was Vince who told me that I had a son.

37:11.080 --> 37:13.640
He thought I knew about it and I just didn't care,

37:13.680 --> 37:16.800
that I was being, you know, same old Jimbo.

37:18.720 --> 37:20.760
When I told Stevie,

37:20.800 --> 37:25.040
I said I couldn't believe I'd had a kid all these years

37:20.800 --> 37:25.040
and never knew about it,

37:25.080 --> 37:27.160
and that's when he come clean.

37:27.200 --> 37:29.600
Told me that he'd known all along.

37:29.640 --> 37:32.000
That's what you were fighting about

37:29.640 --> 37:32.000
in his hotel room?

37:32.040 --> 37:35.440
That's one word for it.

37:38.560 --> 37:43.760
You know, people dream about the lifestyle

37:38.560 --> 37:43.760
that we used to lead.

37:43.800 --> 37:46.840
Partying all night. Girls on tab. It was crazy.

37:48.680 --> 37:53.320
But if all you actually really want is to meet

37:48.680 --> 37:53.320
someone and settle down,

37:53.360 --> 37:56.240
it's not exactly the right environment,

37:53.360 --> 37:56.240
if you know what I mean.

37:56.280 --> 37:57.480
Is that what you wanted?

37:58.200 --> 37:59.640
I'd have loved it.

38:01.760 --> 38:03.840
A wife. A kid.

38:04.880 --> 38:06.200
A family.

38:07.480 --> 38:09.560
Just never seemed to happen.

38:09.600 --> 38:11.320
Well, it did.

38:12.800 --> 38:13.920
Just nobody told me.

38:13.960 --> 38:15.680
So, why didn't Stevie tell you?

38:15.720 --> 38:19.600
Because we'd had a big fight about something

38:15.720 --> 38:19.600
and we weren't talking.

38:19.640 --> 38:22.800
He kept it from me to spite me.

38:22.840 --> 38:26.840
He admitted it. Apologised, even,

38:22.840 --> 38:26.840
which Stevie never does.

38:26.880 --> 38:30.560
Said that he'd messed up years ago and wished he'd

38:26.880 --> 38:30.560
have done things differently.

38:30.600 --> 38:32.000
Said he wanted to put things right.

38:32.040 --> 38:33.400
Did you let him

38:34.440 --> 38:36.560
No. I couldn't. Maybe in time I might have.

38:41.360 --> 38:42.600
But...

38:42.640 --> 38:44.440
So, what did you do?

38:47.280 --> 38:50.080
Hey, hang on. You don't seriously think

38:50.120 --> 38:52.320
I had anything to do with his death, do you?

38:52.360 --> 38:54.920
-Look, I hated Stevie

38:52.360 --> 38:54.920
for what he did.

38:54.960 --> 38:57.640
But he was my brother! I wouldn't kill him!

38:57.680 --> 39:02.280
Look, you want a suspect to talk to,

38:57.680 --> 39:02.280
you've so got the wrong guy.

39:02.320 --> 39:06.280
There's members of this band who've got a real axe to grind

39:02.320 --> 39:06.280
with my brother.

39:25.160 --> 39:26.360
<i>Merci.</i>

39:27.920 --> 39:31.720
It's a little, er, down at heel

39:27.920 --> 39:31.720
for a millionaire.

39:31.760 --> 39:34.200
I like it. It's real.

39:35.960 --> 39:37.440
When we were recording the first album,

39:37.480 --> 39:39.680
me and Stevie used to hang out in places like this.

39:39.720 --> 39:41.440
Jam with the locals.

39:41.480 --> 39:44.240
Ah, great days.

39:44.280 --> 39:47.280
Well, they were, until Stevie got drunk

39:44.280 --> 39:47.280
and wound everyone up.

39:47.320 --> 39:50.400
Jim tells us you started legal proceedings

39:47.320 --> 39:50.400
against Stevie?

39:50.440 --> 39:53.200
It's nothing. Loads of bands end up in courtrooms.

39:53.240 --> 39:56.840
And those cases are usually for huge amounts,

39:53.240 --> 39:56.840
whereas your claim is...

39:56.880 --> 39:58.600
For a pound.

39:58.640 --> 40:02.840
-Pound of flesh'd

39:58.640 --> 40:02.840
be more appropriate.

40:02.880 --> 40:05.760
I didn't want people thinking I was doing it for the money.

40:05.800 --> 40:07.160
Why are you doing it?

40:07.200 --> 40:08.800
Credit.

40:08.840 --> 40:11.000
Aside from one or two tracks on that first album,

40:11.040 --> 40:13.320
we all contributed to the writing and recording.

40:13.360 --> 40:16.000
But you look at the writing credits

40:13.360 --> 40:16.000
for every track and it's...

40:16.040 --> 40:18.360
Lyrics by Stevie, music by Pete?

40:18.400 --> 40:21.600
-Smith and Thunders, yeah. -HUMPHREY: It's a fairly

40:18.400 --> 40:21.600
normal arrangement, isn't it?

40:23.960 --> 40:26.200
I wrote specific lines.

40:26.240 --> 40:29.200
I wrote verses for songs that I took to Stevie.

40:29.240 --> 40:31.480
He said they wouldn't work, and then, a day or so later,

40:31.520 --> 40:33.960
they'd crop up again in another song

40:31.520 --> 40:33.960
that he's written.

40:35.320 --> 40:38.040
I just want to set the record straight.

40:38.960 --> 40:40.640
I want my credit.

40:42.000 --> 40:45.320
There's nothing wrong with wanting that, is there?

40:45.360 --> 40:47.600
Now, if you'll excuse me...

40:59.600 --> 41:01.360
I spoke with Disco's lawyer,

41:01.400 --> 41:04.840
who said it would have been hard to prove that

41:01.400 --> 41:04.840
he co-wrote the songs,

41:04.880 --> 41:08.240
and that instead he should have appealed

41:04.880 --> 41:08.240
to Stevie's goodwill.

41:08.280 --> 41:09.880
Mmm, I wonder where that got him.

41:09.920 --> 41:13.080
Apparently, Stevie told Disco he'd amend the credit listing

41:13.120 --> 41:15.920
on any reissue of the first album.

41:15.960 --> 41:18.640
But then the record company just sent this over.

41:20.280 --> 41:22.840
It's the design for the reissued

41:20.280 --> 41:22.840
album artwork,

41:22.880 --> 41:25.560
and, as you'll see, no mention of Disco Biscuit.

41:25.600 --> 41:27.400
Has Disco seen this?

41:27.440 --> 41:30.400
All band members were sent an early copy for approval

41:27.440 --> 41:30.400
two days ago.

41:30.440 --> 41:33.480
So, Disco Biscuit knew that Stevie was shafting him?

41:33.520 --> 41:35.800
Which is fine, is fine,

41:35.840 --> 41:38.840
but while he may have had a motive, he didn't

41:35.840 --> 41:38.840
have the opportunity.

41:38.880 --> 41:40.360
See, from the recordings,

41:40.400 --> 41:42.320
we know that Disco was in the studio

41:40.400 --> 41:42.320
when the power went out.

41:42.360 --> 41:43.920
-As was Vince. -Yes, I know.

41:43.960 --> 41:45.400
-And Pete and Cheryl. -Yes, thank you.

41:45.440 --> 41:46.720
-And Jim. -Yes, I know.

41:46.760 --> 41:49.040
FLORENCE: None of them had the opportunity.

41:52.080 --> 41:54.000
HUMPHREY: "Lee Vale Productions."

41:55.400 --> 41:58.400
Lee Vale. Lee Vale.

41:59.520 --> 42:01.560
Where have I heard that name before?

42:01.600 --> 42:03.280
Who is this Lee Vale?

42:03.320 --> 42:06.800
No, Lee Vale isn't a person. It's, er, some kind

42:03.320 --> 42:06.800
of record company.

42:06.840 --> 42:10.960
Lee Vale Productions. They're behind the reissue

42:06.840 --> 42:10.960
of the album. Lee Vale.

42:11.000 --> 42:13.280
-Yes.

42:13.320 --> 42:16.320
Er, 17 Lee Vale, Marston, Oxford...

42:19.720 --> 42:21.760
Of course. <i> Flower Seeds.</i>

42:25.160 --> 42:26.640
-Here. -And here.

42:26.680 --> 42:28.520
"Edited by Daisy Buttercup." Her address is...

42:28.560 --> 42:30.840
"17 Lee Vale, Marston, Oxford."

42:30.880 --> 42:33.120
So, Daisy Buttercup is Lee Vale Productions?

42:33.160 --> 42:36.960
-The one and the same. -So, who is this notorious

42:33.160 --> 42:36.960
Miss Daisy Buttercup?

42:37.960 --> 42:39.520
I know.

42:42.520 --> 42:44.520
HUMPHREY: Thank you for your time, Cheryl.

42:44.560 --> 42:47.000
Or do you prefer "Daisy Buttercup"?

42:49.920 --> 42:52.520
I'm sorry. I'm going to have to go

42:49.920 --> 42:52.520
and, erm, change.

42:52.560 --> 42:54.840
Oh, no, don't worry. It will soon dry in the sun.

42:56.440 --> 42:58.600
Care to bring us up to speed about how Daisy,

42:58.640 --> 43:03.000
the number

43:03.040 --> 43:05.760
Disco Biscuit bought my house. That's, er, how we met and...

43:05.800 --> 43:07.600
And according to our research,

43:07.640 --> 43:11.400
you've been in the music business

43:07.640 --> 43:11.400
for three months.

43:11.440 --> 43:14.760
I know I'm not exactly what you'd call, er,

43:11.440 --> 43:14.760
qualified, but...

43:14.800 --> 43:16.880
I have very good organisational skills

43:16.920 --> 43:20.400
and when I set my mind to something,

43:16.920 --> 43:20.400
I make sure it happens.

43:20.440 --> 43:21.840
I got the band back together again.

43:21.880 --> 43:23.840
I did the deal with the beer company.

43:23.880 --> 43:26.920
I mean, even yesterday, Stevie was saying he wasn't

43:23.880 --> 43:26.920
going to sign the contract.

43:26.960 --> 43:29.520
But, you know, then, when it came to it, he did.

43:31.160 --> 43:33.680
I mean, I... I made that happen.

43:33.720 --> 43:36.880
This must be a dream come true for you.

43:37.320 --> 43:38.960
Sorry?

43:39.000 --> 43:41.560
Managing the one rock band you've spent

43:39.000 --> 43:41.560
your life following.

43:41.600 --> 43:42.880
Adoring.

43:42.920 --> 43:45.920
Yeah, I guess I'm very fortunate.

43:45.960 --> 43:48.280
And who in the band knew that as well as their manager,

43:48.320 --> 43:50.440
you're actually their biggest fan?

43:51.960 --> 43:53.240
None of them.

43:53.280 --> 43:56.160
So, what exactly were you up to?

43:56.200 --> 43:58.160
Sorry, I don't know what you mean.

43:58.200 --> 44:01.240
Well, I mean, come on. Your behaviour is verging

43:58.200 --> 44:01.240
on that of a stalker.

44:02.240 --> 44:05.760
That... That is not true.

44:05.800 --> 44:09.720
I... I just wanted to try something new...

44:05.800 --> 44:09.720
I just... With my life.

44:09.760 --> 44:12.440
You know, try something different.

44:12.480 --> 44:14.760
You did it to get close to Stevie, didn't you?

44:16.960 --> 44:19.200
What?

44:19.240 --> 44:23.560
That necklace, I've seen it before.

44:23.600 --> 44:27.160
Grand Central Beer? I'm no sell-out,

44:23.600 --> 44:27.160
especially not that stuff.

44:27.200 --> 44:29.000
It's crap!

44:29.040 --> 44:30.880
It belonged to Stevie, didn't it?

44:31.560 --> 44:33.080
He gave it to me. Seems quite

44:33.120 --> 44:34.640
a personal kind of gift.

44:36.360 --> 44:38.200
Were you and Stevie having a relationship?

44:41.640 --> 44:43.160
I fell for him.

44:44.960 --> 44:46.960
I'd always had a crush on him since I was a...

44:47.000 --> 44:49.360
A kid. But I thought I was over it,

44:49.400 --> 44:53.560
and then, you know, we met, and he just swept me

44:49.400 --> 44:53.560
off my feet.

44:53.600 --> 44:54.920
And then?

44:55.840 --> 44:57.400
He, um...

44:57.440 --> 44:59.120
He... He ended it.

45:00.560 --> 45:03.800
He'd fallen in love with the band again, you see,

45:03.840 --> 45:07.160
and, you know, he needed to concentrate on that.

45:07.200 --> 45:10.680
HUMPHREY: <i> And were you</i> <i>okay with him ending it?</i>

45:11.480 --> 45:12.880
No!

45:12.920 --> 45:13.920
I was not okay.

45:15.440 --> 45:18.160
Yeah, okay, I admit it.

45:15.440 --> 45:18.160
I was in love with him.

45:18.200 --> 45:20.760
And that's exactly why I wouldn't have killed him.

45:24.080 --> 45:28.120
The answer has to be here, somewhere.

45:29.680 --> 45:33.160
Stevie Smith had a fling with Cheryl Moore,

45:29.680 --> 45:33.160
number-one fan.

45:33.200 --> 45:35.040
Breaks her heart.

45:35.080 --> 45:38.000
Disco Biscuit's suing Stevie for not crediting him.

45:38.040 --> 45:41.440
Jim Smith could have been a father,

45:38.040 --> 45:41.440
had Stevie not hushed it up.

45:41.480 --> 45:44.240
Vince. Stevie burnt his studio down.

45:44.280 --> 45:46.840
All of them have a motive. But none of them

45:46.880 --> 45:49.440
had the opportunity.

45:49.480 --> 45:51.560
At 12:00, Stevie was having his daily swim.

45:51.600 --> 45:56.320
One of the suspects pushes live stage lights into

45:51.600 --> 45:56.320
the pool, electrocuting him.

45:56.360 --> 45:58.800
They then sawed one of the support pins in half,

45:58.840 --> 46:00.560
in an attempt to make it look like it had,

46:00.600 --> 46:02.440
after years of use, finally broken,

46:02.480 --> 46:04.760
meaning Stevie's death looked like an awful accident.

46:04.800 --> 46:08.640
But... But for that very reason, we know

46:04.800 --> 46:08.640
he was actually murdered,

46:08.680 --> 46:10.400
and the only five people who could have done it

46:10.440 --> 46:12.920
were all together in the studio when it happened,

46:12.960 --> 46:16.160
thus presenting us with what is, it would seem,

46:12.960 --> 46:16.160
an impossible murder.

46:16.200 --> 46:18.320
We are getting nowhere!

46:20.840 --> 46:24.240
Let's take a break, clear our heads.

46:28.240 --> 46:29.600
And you're not helping matters.

46:30.680 --> 46:32.080
I mean, why were you there?

46:32.120 --> 46:34.320
Why were you at our crime scene?

46:35.840 --> 46:38.440
-You're talking to a dead beetle.

46:35.840 --> 46:38.440
-I know I am.

46:38.480 --> 46:40.280
Do you think maybe you should get some fresh air?

46:40.320 --> 46:42.440
That's probably a very good idea.

46:58.520 --> 46:59.520
Ah, sir?

47:07.880 --> 47:09.560
It will soon dry in the sun.

47:13.040 --> 47:14.880
HUMPHREY: Why were you at our crime scene?

47:14.920 --> 47:17.800
Maybe he ended up on a boat or a plane

47:14.920 --> 47:17.800
and got carried over.

47:17.840 --> 47:20.640
I think the pin snapped and the whole thing fell

47:17.840 --> 47:20.640
into the swimming pool.

47:20.680 --> 47:21.760
Ha!

47:22.480 --> 47:24.320
Right.

47:29.400 --> 47:31.320
Of course.

47:31.360 --> 47:35.360
The last time anyone is heard leaving the studio

47:31.360 --> 47:35.360
after Stevie is 10:00.

47:35.400 --> 47:38.760
Stevie was excited, reenergised.

47:38.800 --> 47:40.560
Said he wanted to put things right.

47:40.600 --> 47:43.080
Yesterday, Stevie was saying he wasn't going to sign

47:40.600 --> 47:43.080
the contract,

47:43.120 --> 47:45.240
but when it came to it, he did.

47:47.840 --> 47:49.560
STEVIE: Grand Central Beer?

47:49.600 --> 47:53.200
No way. I'm no sell-out, especially not that stuff.

47:49.600 --> 47:53.200
It's crap!

47:56.000 --> 47:58.520
Yes, I think I have. We need to get

47:56.000 --> 47:58.520
everyone together.

47:58.560 --> 48:02.040
But first I need to check something in the studio.

48:02.080 --> 48:05.080
Oh, and, Dwayne, catering. You want me to bring food?

48:05.120 --> 48:09.000
The company who provided the catering equipment at the

48:05.120 --> 48:09.000
studio, dig out their details.

48:09.040 --> 48:10.480
Come on, JP!

48:24.280 --> 48:26.000
Got it. Bag it.

48:35.840 --> 48:36.960
Good.

48:45.920 --> 48:46.960
Yes.

48:49.600 --> 48:51.600
Okay.

48:51.640 --> 48:56.200
First off, apologies for bringing you all out here to

48:51.640 --> 48:56.200
the scene of Stevie's murder.

48:56.240 --> 49:01.440
Now, I know he was a good friend to all of you,

48:56.240 --> 49:01.440
a brother to some of you.

49:01.480 --> 49:03.880
So, why would any of you want to kill him?

49:04.760 --> 49:06.720
-Cheryl... -I didn't do it!

49:06.760 --> 49:08.880
...AKA Daisy Buttercup.

49:08.920 --> 49:12.480
Number-one fan. Editor of the fanzine

49:08.920 --> 49:12.480
<i>Flower Seeds.</i>

49:12.520 --> 49:15.960
-Responsible for

49:12.520 --> 49:15.960
reuniting the band. -I'm no killer.

49:16.000 --> 49:19.440
-But you are Stevie's biggest fan.

49:19.480 --> 49:24.000
And his lover, briefly, before he broke your heart.

49:24.040 --> 49:27.840
Vince? You strike me as being a very patient man,

49:27.880 --> 49:30.920
biding your time, waiting for Stevie to return,

49:30.960 --> 49:33.360
the man who burned down your studio and ruined you.

49:33.400 --> 49:36.880
I couldn't kill Stevie.

49:33.400 --> 49:36.880
I couldn't kill anyone.

49:36.920 --> 49:39.240
And Disco Biscuit.

49:39.280 --> 49:41.680
I'd prefer it if you call me Duncan.

49:41.720 --> 49:44.760
-I wouldn't.

49:44.800 --> 49:48.080
Even though your contribution to the band has never

49:44.800 --> 49:48.080
been recognised?

49:48.120 --> 49:51.320
Stevie still ensured the reissued CD

49:48.120 --> 49:51.320
didn't credit you.

49:51.360 --> 49:53.560
I was in the studio when Stevie was killed.

49:53.600 --> 49:55.280
Of course you were.

49:55.320 --> 49:57.760
Rock-solid alibi, same as everyone else.

49:57.800 --> 50:00.040
And Jim.

50:01.640 --> 50:05.280
Stevie deprived you of the one thing

50:01.640 --> 50:05.280
you wanted in life.

50:06.640 --> 50:08.120
A family.

50:08.160 --> 50:10.440
I told you, Stevie was my brother.

50:10.480 --> 50:12.520
I wouldn't have hurt him.

50:12.560 --> 50:13.640
No.

50:14.440 --> 50:17.000
No, but Pete would.

50:17.040 --> 50:19.880
We know you attacked Stevie in Cardiff

50:17.040 --> 50:19.880
when the band split,

50:19.920 --> 50:21.960
and we also know that Stevie potentially costing you

50:22.000 --> 50:24.160
the beer commercial money was "Cardiff again."

50:29.400 --> 50:31.320
And now we know you murdered him.

50:36.480 --> 50:38.160
You what?

50:38.200 --> 50:40.720
Grand Central Beer brought you all back together,

50:40.760 --> 50:43.040
and it pushed you all apart again, didn't it?

50:43.080 --> 50:46.440
It was an accident! What are you going on about?

50:46.480 --> 50:49.720
Stevie may have initially been seduced by a quick payday,

50:50.680 --> 50:52.880
but then things changed for him.

50:52.920 --> 50:55.920
No way. I'm no sell-out, especially not that stuff.

50:55.960 --> 50:59.840
I told you, the beer company are delighted with

50:55.960 --> 50:59.840
that little clip.

50:59.880 --> 51:02.040
But there was a bigger problem than the bad press

51:02.080 --> 51:03.880
that clip might have brought you, wasn't there?

51:04.600 --> 51:07.080
Stevie, the new Stevie

51:08.560 --> 51:10.200
didn't want to sell out.

51:10.240 --> 51:11.320
He was still a man of the people...

51:13.840 --> 51:16.680
And because of that, he refused to sign

51:13.840 --> 51:16.680
that contract.

51:16.720 --> 51:19.680
But I told you, he did. He did sign the contract.

51:19.720 --> 51:21.480
And you saw Stevie sign it?

51:22.240 --> 51:23.320
No.

51:25.680 --> 51:28.960
-Pete did. -FLORENCE:

51:25.680 --> 51:28.960
The date on the contract

51:29.000 --> 51:31.960
indicates that Stevie signed it yesterday morning.

51:32.000 --> 51:34.000
HUMPHREY: He was pretty adamant in that recording.

51:34.040 --> 51:37.760
I think he had no intention of changing his mind

51:34.040 --> 51:37.760
and signing that contract,

51:37.800 --> 51:39.760
and that is why you had to kill him,

51:40.960 --> 51:42.440
so you could forge his signature

51:42.480 --> 51:44.680
and collect the half a million dollars

51:42.480 --> 51:44.680
you so needed.

51:44.720 --> 51:48.720
This is ridiculous. How would I forge

51:44.720 --> 51:48.720
his signature?

51:48.760 --> 51:52.320
Oh, it's not that hard. I mean, not if you

51:48.760 --> 51:52.320
had the means.

51:55.520 --> 51:58.640
Just place this under the contract where

51:55.520 --> 51:58.640
Stevie's signature should be,

51:58.680 --> 52:01.400
and just trace it over.

52:01.440 --> 52:03.400
The thing is, if you had done it that way,

52:03.440 --> 52:05.440
er, then you would be able to see the indentations

52:05.480 --> 52:07.360
where you went over Stevie's signature.

52:07.400 --> 52:09.600
Erm, there.

52:14.000 --> 52:18.400
Half a million dollars split between you and Stevie.

52:18.440 --> 52:22.080
Plus the prospect of capitalising on the advert,

52:18.440 --> 52:22.080
and touring.

52:22.120 --> 52:24.240
How are we going to tour without a singer?

52:24.280 --> 52:26.320
This band is nothing without Stevie.

52:26.360 --> 52:29.200
Oh, I don't think you believe that for a second.

52:29.240 --> 52:33.120
That's why you made sure that Stevie died

52:29.240 --> 52:33.120
in such an iconic way.

52:33.160 --> 52:35.880
Electrocuted in a swimming pool. Legend!

52:38.880 --> 52:40.520
I mean, the publicity and the attention

52:38.880 --> 52:40.520
would be enormous.

52:40.560 --> 52:42.400
You would clean up.

52:42.440 --> 52:45.080
But Pete was with us in the studio when Stevie was...

52:45.120 --> 52:46.720
HUMPHREY: Was murdered, yes.

52:49.080 --> 52:50.520
DISCO: Oh, come on!

52:52.200 --> 52:53.280
That was the clever part.

52:56.120 --> 52:59.400
How could someone be at the pool to push

52:56.120 --> 52:59.400
the stage lights in

52:59.440 --> 53:02.320
when all of you were in the studio the entire morning?

53:03.600 --> 53:04.640
All except for you, Pete.

53:07.000 --> 53:09.320
It was around 10:00 when you popped out,

53:09.360 --> 53:12.080
perfect time to set your trap.

53:12.120 --> 53:15.160
Your intention was for us to assume that the whole thing

53:12.120 --> 53:15.160
was an accident,

53:15.200 --> 53:17.600
a worn pin snapping after years of use.

53:17.640 --> 53:21.160
I think the pin snapped and the whole thing

53:17.640 --> 53:21.160
fell into the swimming pool.

53:21.200 --> 53:25.000
And that's how we knew it was murder all along.

53:26.160 --> 53:27.400
The pin

53:28.480 --> 53:31.840
had been very clearly cut with a saw.

53:33.480 --> 53:34.640
Which brings us to...

53:41.480 --> 53:46.120
...the click beetle, who was an unknowing

53:41.480 --> 53:46.120
accomplice to murder.

53:46.160 --> 53:48.080
You see, when we first arrived on the crime scene,

53:48.120 --> 53:50.120
it bothered me that there was water

53:50.160 --> 53:52.840
in the planter that was sitting in front

53:50.160 --> 53:52.840
of the fallen lighting stand,

53:52.880 --> 53:54.400
but not in any of the others.

53:56.600 --> 54:00.080
The supply company Cheryl used for the party,

53:56.600 --> 54:00.080
we checked it.

54:00.120 --> 54:02.240
Some of the gear came from Martinique.

54:02.280 --> 54:04.560
It was the same island our click beetle came from.

54:04.600 --> 54:07.400
You know, I think he hopped into the catering equipment,

54:07.440 --> 54:10.600
a freezer, to be specific, and got shipped over,

54:10.640 --> 54:13.480
and so our little beetle here

54:13.520 --> 54:16.680
ended up encased in a block of ice.

54:16.720 --> 54:20.760
<i>In fact, the one particular</i> <i>block of ice you used</i>

54:16.720 --> 54:20.760
<i>to kill Stevie Smith.</i>

54:20.800 --> 54:23.040
<i>Earlier in the morning</i> <i>at 10:00,</i>

54:23.080 --> 54:26.000
<i>knowing that Stevie would</i> <i>take his daily swim at noon,</i>

54:26.040 --> 54:28.640
<i>you used one of the caterer's</i> <i>blocks of ice</i>

54:28.680 --> 54:31.560
<i>to rest one of the legs</i> <i>of the lighting stand on,</i>

54:31.600 --> 54:34.240
<i>and as the sun was</i> <i>at its midday height,</i>

54:35.680 --> 54:38.600
<i>the ice would melt,</i> <i>the support would fail...</i>

54:39.840 --> 54:42.320
<i>...Stevie would be</i> <i>electrocuted.</i>

54:42.360 --> 54:45.760
And with the planter placed at the front of the stage,

54:45.800 --> 54:49.000
you'd even planned a place for the melted water

54:45.800 --> 54:49.000
to drain off,

54:49.040 --> 54:50.720
leaving no trace.

54:50.760 --> 54:52.640
Well, er...

54:53.600 --> 54:54.760
Almost no trace.

55:02.640 --> 55:04.760
Hats off to you, Mr Thunders.

55:06.360 --> 55:08.320
You really gave us a run for our money.

55:09.680 --> 55:11.280
Very entertaining.

55:13.360 --> 55:16.120
But what a load of... Rubbish.

55:18.400 --> 55:19.600
Is it?

55:21.240 --> 55:22.920
No.

55:22.960 --> 55:26.080
You... You don't do that to me.

55:28.480 --> 55:30.760
That man! That idiot!

55:30.800 --> 55:32.480
I'm the artist!

55:32.520 --> 55:36.880
Every bad thing that ever happened

55:32.520 --> 55:36.880
to us was because of him!

55:44.440 --> 55:46.000
Can't... Can't swim!

55:47.640 --> 55:49.120
Hold your feet down!

56:02.560 --> 56:03.760
Chief!

56:05.800 --> 56:07.920
JP seems to have fitted in well.

56:07.960 --> 56:09.600
Well, yeah, er... Yes, Florence.

56:09.640 --> 56:11.560
He's... He's not the only one, though.

56:11.600 --> 56:16.760
Er, I have to say that you have been absolutely,

56:11.600 --> 56:16.760
unquestionably brilliant

56:16.800 --> 56:17.880
over the last two days.

56:17.920 --> 56:19.040
Thank you.

56:19.080 --> 56:21.280
No, I mean, the way you handled Cheryl.

56:21.320 --> 56:23.480
Spotting the necklace. Her affair with Stevie.

56:23.520 --> 56:25.120
It's just phenomenal.

56:25.160 --> 56:28.960
And then there's, well, everything else, really.

56:29.000 --> 56:31.720
Every time I've lost the plot or couldn't find

56:29.000 --> 56:31.720
a piece of evidence,

56:31.760 --> 56:34.280
or literally have nowhere to turn, there you were.

56:34.320 --> 56:38.160
I mean, I... I mean, it's like we've been partners for years.

56:39.920 --> 56:41.720
What

56:43.560 --> 56:45.600
I have a confession.

56:45.640 --> 56:48.080
I received a letter from Camille.

56:48.120 --> 56:49.600
Oh?

56:49.640 --> 56:52.120
Yeah. With very detailed instructions on how to

56:49.640 --> 56:52.120
deal with you.

56:53.520 --> 56:56.320
So, if there's anyone you should thank, it's her.

56:56.360 --> 56:59.840
Well, even so, very well done.

56:59.880 --> 57:03.120
Congratulations on completing your first case as a DS.

57:03.160 --> 57:05.160
-To you. -To Camille.

57:05.200 --> 57:06.360
To you both.

57:08.280 --> 57:12.520
Although... Although you are already a great DS,

57:12.560 --> 57:15.080
and I'm sure will become an even better DS,

57:15.120 --> 57:17.360
there are many, many more things

57:15.120 --> 57:17.360
you need to learn

57:17.400 --> 57:19.320
before becoming a truly amazing DS.

57:19.360 --> 57:22.080
I know. I know there's so much work to do and...

57:22.120 --> 57:24.200
I'm not talking about work.

57:24.240 --> 57:26.640
Every good detective should have their dancing shoes on,

57:26.680 --> 57:28.600
and this is a good and happy tune. Come on.

57:28.640 --> 57:30.160
-No. -Come on.

57:32.000 --> 57:34.360
<i>(BOOM-SHA-KA-LACKA</i> BY TOMMY MCCOOK

57:32.000 --> 57:34.360
AND HOPETON LEWIS PLAYING)

58:07.440 --> 58:09.960
DWAYNE: <i> It's been 15 years</i> <i>since we were last</i>

58:07.440 --> 58:09.960
<i>in the final.</i>

58:10.000 --> 58:11.960
<i>It's been going on</i> <i>for generations.</i>

58:12.000 --> 58:13.400
-Yeah! -HUMPHREY:

58:12.000 --> 58:13.400
I'm not completely ignorant

58:13.440 --> 58:16.320
when it comes to international sports, you know.

58:16.360 --> 58:20.160
Honour and sportsmanship is the nature of the game,

58:20.200 --> 58:22.560
not always the nature of those that play it.

58:22.600 --> 58:24.360
-This is Anton Borridge. -Er, Burrage.

58:24.400 --> 58:28.040
He is an odious little toad.

58:29.720 --> 58:30.880
AIDEN: <i> There is nothing</i> <i>Hank wouldn't do</i>

58:29.720 --> 58:30.880
<i>to win that trophy.</i>
